        <definition>XUartPsv_Config * XUartPsv_LookupConfig</definition>
        <argsstring>(UINTPTR BaseAddress)</argsstring>
        <name>XUartPsv_LookupConfig</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Looks up the device configuration based on the unique device ID/BaseAddress. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The XUartPsv_ConfigTable[] contains the configuration info for each device in the system.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the base address of the device</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the configuration found or NULL if the specified device ID/BaseAddress was not found. See <ref refid="xuartpsv_8h" kindref="compound">xuartpsv.h</ref> for the definition of <ref refid="struct_x_uart_psv___config" kindref="compound">XUartPsv_Config</ref>.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>In XSCT/classic flow, DeviceId is used to look up the device configuration. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
